&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Education:&lt;/strong&gt; A bachelor’s degree or equivalent work experience in human rights, international relations, social science, or a related field is required.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Experience:&lt;/strong&gt; A minimum of one (1) year of relevant work experience is required.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Related Skills and Knowledge:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prior office/administration experience and strong organizational skills are required.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent oral and written communication skills in English are required; fluency in an Asian language is preferred.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong interest in Asia and international human rights is required. Asia-related experience is desirable.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong interpersonal skills and the ability to work well under pressure while juggling multiple tasks simultaneously are required.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to make sound decisions consistent with functions is required.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to prioritize with minimal supervision and work independently as well as function as a member of a team with staff in multiple locations globally is required.&lt;/li&gt;
