&lt;p&gt;The COO will directly supervise the following organizational functions Finance &amp;amp; Accounting, Global Financial Operations, Information Security &amp;amp; Technology, General Counsel, People&amp;amp; Culture, Real Estate, and Security. In addition, they will have oversight authority to ensure HRW’s compliance with the highest organizational management standards, including rigorous budgetary and financial accounting processes; professional conduct at all levels; and a deep commitment to diversity, equity, and inclusion, as well as the personal and professional growth of staff. Together with the Operations Leadership Team (OLT), which comprises the leaders of all the operations functions, the COO will ensure effective, transparent, and inclusive communication processes, including seeking input and feedback across HRW on the design and implementation of organization-wide policies and initiatives.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;KEY RESPONSIBILITIES&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
